HEADWORD: Carrigeen
<hw>Car"ri*geen`</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr> }</mhw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A small, purplish, branching,
cartilaginous seaweed (<spn>Chondrus crispus</spn>), which, when
bleached, is the <altname>Irish moss</altname> of commerce.</def>
<altsp>[Also written <asp>carragheen</asp>,
<asp>carageen</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

